description: Product_{q|n} [p(q)] divides p(n), where p(n) is number of unrestricted partitions of n and the product is over all distinct primes q that divide n.
example: 10 is included because p(10) = 42 is divisible by p(2)*p(5) = 2*7 and 2 and 5 are the distinct prime divisors of 10.
